<!-- Stonetop character sheet for Roll20. Based on Stonetop by Jeremy Strandberg, CCBYSA 4.0. Sheet customizations by Morcoire. -->

<div class="stonetop-main">
  <input type="hidden" class="stonetop-tabstoggle" name="attr_sheetTab" value="character" />
  <div class="stonetop-tabs" aria-hidden="true">
    <button type="action" name="act_character" class="character">Character</button>
    <button type="action" name="act_inventory" class="inventory">Inventory</button>
    <button type="action" name="act_followers" class="followers">Followers</button>
  </div>

  <div class="stonetop-character-section">
    <h1 class="stonetop-sr-only">Character</h1>

    <input type="hidden" name="attr_activeplaybook" value="none">

    <div class="stonetop-header-row">
      <label class="stonetop-character-name heading-field">
        <span>Name:</span>
        <input type="text" name="attr_character_name" />
      </label>
      <div class="stonetop-playbook-title-display">
        <span class="playbook-display-label heavy-label">The Heavy</span>
        <span class="playbook-display-label fox-label">The Fox</span>
        <span class="playbook-display-label wbh-label">The Would-Be Hero</span>
        <span class="playbook-display-label blessed-label">The Blessed</span>
        <span class="playbook-display-label judge-label">The Judge</span>
        <span class="playbook-display-label lightbearer-label">The Lightbearer</span>
        <span class="playbook-display-label marshal-label">The Marshal</span>
        <span class="playbook-display-label ranger-label">The Ranger</span>
        <span class="playbook-display-label seeker-label">The Seeker</span>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="stonetop-row">
      <div class="stonetop-column-thirds">
        <label class="heading-field">
          <span>Player Name:</span>
          <input type="text" name="attr_player_name" />
        </label>
      </div>
      <div class="stonetop-column-thirds">
        <label class="heading-field">
          <span>Playbook:</span>
          <select name="attr_class">
            <option disabled selected>Select One</option>
            <option value="blessed">The Blessed</option>
            <option value="fox">The Fox</option>
            <option value="heavy">The Heavy</option>
            <option value="judge">The Judge</option>
            <option value="lightbearer">The Lightbearer</option>
            <option value="marshal">The Marshal</option>
            <option value="ranger">The Ranger</option>
            <option value="seeker">The Seeker</option>
            <option value="would-be-hero">The Would-Be Hero</option>
          </select>
        </label>
      </div>
      <div class="stonetop-column-thirds">
        <div class="stonetop-row stonetop-xp">
          <label>
            <span>XP:</span>
            <input type="number" name="attr_xp" value="0" />
          </label>
          <label class="level">
            <span>Level:</span>
            <input type="number" name="attr_level" value="1" />
          </label>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="stonetop-row">
      <div class="stonetop-column-thirds">
        <label class="heading-field">
          Background:
          <input type="text" name="attr_background">
        </label>
      </div>
      <div class="stonetop-column-thirds">
        <label class="heading-field">
          Instinct:
          <input type="text" name="attr_drive">
        </label>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="stonetop-row">
      <h3>Stats</h3>
    </div>
    
    <div class="stonetop-row">
      <div class="stonetop-stat">
        <div class="octagon bg"></div>
        <div class="octagon"></div>
        <div class="stonetop-stat-content">
          <label for="strength">Strength</label>
          <input id="strength" type="number" name="attr_str" value="0" />
          <button type="roll" name="roll_STRCheck" value="/em uses Strength, and rolls [[?{Roll Type | Standard, 2d6 + @{str} | Advantage, 3d6d1 + @{str} | Disadvantage, 3d6dh1 + @{str}}]]"></button>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="stonetop-stat">
        <div class="octagon bg"></div>
        <div class="octagon"></div>
        <div class="stonetop-stat-content">
          <label for="dexterity">Dexterity</label>
          <input id="dexterity" type="number" name="attr_dex" value="0" />
          <button type="roll" name="roll_DEXCheck" value="/em uses Dexterity, and rolls [[?{Roll Type | Standard, 2d6 + @{dex} | Advantage, 3d6d1 + @{dex} | Disadvantage, 3d6dh1 + @{dex}}]]"></button>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="stonetop-stat">
        <div class="octagon bg"></div>
        <div class="octagon"></div>
        <div class="stonetop-stat-content">
          <label for="intelligence">Intelligence</label>
          <input id="intelligence" type="number" name="attr_int" value="0" />
          <button type="roll" name="roll_INTCheck" value="/em uses Intelligence, and rolls [[?{Roll Type | Standard, 2d6 + @{int} | Advantage, 3d6d1 + @{int} | Disadvantage, 3d6dh1 + @{int}}]]"></button>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="stonetop-stat">
        <div class="octagon bg"></div>
        <div class="octagon"></div>
        <div class="stonetop-stat-content">
          <label for="wisdom">Wisdom</label>
          <input id="wisdom" type="number" name="attr_wis" value="0" />
          <button type="roll" name="roll_WISCheck" value="/em uses Wisdom, and rolls [[?{Roll Type | Standard, 2d6 + @{wis} | Advantage, 3d6d1 + @{wis} | Disadvantage, 3d6dh1 + @{wis}}]]"></button>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="stonetop-stat">
        <div class="octagon bg"></div>
        <div class="octagon"></div>
        <div class="stonetop-stat-content">
          <label for="constitution">Constitution</label>
          <input id="constitution" type="number" name="attr_con" value="0" />
          <button type="roll" name="roll_CONCheck" value="/em uses Constitution, and rolls [[?{Roll Type | Standard, 2d6 + @{con} | Advantage, 3d6d1 + @{con} | Disadvantage, 3d6dh1 + @{con}}]]"></button>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="stonetop-stat">
        <div class="octagon bg"></div>
        <div class="octagon"></div>
        <div class="stonetop-stat-content">
          <label for="charisma">Charisma</label>
          <input id="charisma" type="number" name="attr_cha" value="0" />
          <button type="roll" name="roll_CHACheck" value="/em uses Charisma, and rolls [[?{Roll Type | Standard, 2d6 + @{cha} | Advantage, 3d6d1 + @{cha} | Disadvantage, 3d6dh1 + @{cha}}]]"></button>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Debilities unchanged -->
    <div class="stonetop-row">
      <div class="stonetop-column-thirds">
        <div class="stonetop-debility">
          <div class="stonetop-grouping-image"></div>
          <label>
            <div class="stonetop-checkbox-wrapper">
              <input type="checkbox" name="attr_weakened" value="yes">
            </div>
            <span>Weakened</span>
          </label>
          <span class="description">(take Disadvantage)</span>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="stonetop-column-thirds">
        <div class="stonetop-debility">
          <div class="stonetop-grouping-image"></div>
          <label>
            <div class="stonetop-checkbox-wrapper">
              <input type="checkbox" name="attr_dazed" value="yes">
            </div>
            <span>Dazed</span>
          </label>
          <span class="description">(take Disadvantage)</span>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="stonetop-column-thirds">
        <div class="stonetop-debility">
          <div class="stonetop-grouping-image"></div>
          <label>
            <div class="stonetop-checkbox-wrapper">
              <input type="checkbox" name="attr_miserable" value="yes">
            </div>
            <span>Miserable</span>
          </label>
          <span class="description">(take Disadvantage)</span>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- CHANGE 3: Compact stats row — replaces tall HP block, Notes removed -->
    <div class="stonetop-compact-stats">
      <div class="stonetop-hp-compact">
        <div class="stonetop-current-hp">
          <div class="octagon bg"></div>
          <div class="octagon"></div>
          <div class="stonetop-hp-content">
            <span name="attr_hp"></span>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="stonetop-hp-fields">
          <label class="compact-field">
            <span>Max HP:</span>
            <input type="number" name="attr_hpmax" value="0" />
          </label>
          <label class="compact-field">
            <span>Damage Taken:</span>
            <input type="number" name="attr_damagetaken" value="0" />
          </label>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="stonetop-damage-compact">
        <span class="compact-label-top">Do Damage</span>
        <button type="roll" name="roll_damage" value="/em causes damage, and rolls [[@{damagedie}]]"></button>
        <select name="attr_damagedie" class="stonetop-damagedie">
          <option value="0">No Damage</option>
          <option value="d4">D4</option>
          <option value="d6">D6</option>
          <option value="d8">D8</option>
          <option value="d10">D10</option>
          <option value="d12">D12</option>
        </select>
      </div>
      <div class="stonetop-armor-compact">
        <span class="compact-label-top">Armor</span>
        <input type="number" name="attr_armor" value="0" />
      </div>
    </div>



    <!-- ========== HEAVY PLAYBOOK ========== -->
    <div class="stonetop-playbook-section heavy-section">
      <h2>The Heavy</h2>
      <p class="playbook-reminder"><strong>Damage:</strong> d10 &nbsp;|&nbsp; <strong>HP Max:</strong> 20</p>
      <p class="playbook-note">You start with <strong>Dangerous</strong> and <strong>Hard to Kill</strong>, plus either <strong>Armored</strong> or <strong>Uncanny Reflexes</strong>.</p>
      <h3>Moves</h3>
      <div class="stonetop-moves-list">
        <div class="stonetop-move">
          <label><input type="checkbox" name="attr_heavy_armored"> <strong>Armored</strong> (Starting choice)</label>
          <p>When you carry a shield, mark only ✔ (instead of ✔✔). Also, ignore the <em>cumbersome</em> tag on any armor you wear. If taken at start of play, add an iron hauberk, bronze cuirass, or scale coat to inventory (all 2 armor, warm, cumbersome).</p>
        </div>
        <div class="stonetop-move">
          <label><input type="checkbox" name="attr_heavy_battlejoy"> <strong>Battle Joy</strong></label>
          <p>When you <em>spill blood and lose yourself in battle</em>, ignore fear, pain, mind-control, and debility effects while fighting. When action stops, roll +CON: 10+, regain 1d4 HP; 7-9, winded but fine; 6-, mark a debility but don't mark XP.</p>
          <button type="roll" name="roll_heavy_battlejoy" value="/em uses Battle Joy, rolling +CON [[2d6+@{con}]]"></button>
        </div>
        <div class="stonetop-move stonetop-move-indent">
          <label><input type="checkbox" name="attr_heavy_berserker"> <strong>Berserker</strong> (Requires Battle Joy)</label>
          <p>While in Battle Joy, add the <em>area</em> tag to melee attacks. Roll damage separately for each target.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="stonetop-move">
          <label><input type="checkbox" name="attr_heavy_carvedoutofwood"> <strong>Carved Out of Wood</strong></label>
          <p>Increase your max HP by 4.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="stonetop-move">
          <label><input type="checkbox" name="attr_heavy_dangerous" checked> <strong>Dangerous ★</strong> (Starting move)</label>
          <p>When you <em>deal your damage</em>, you have advantage.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="stonetop-move">
          <label><input type="checkbox" name="attr_heavy_formidable"> <strong>Formidable</strong></label>
          <p>When you <em>wade into battle</em>, roll +CHA: 10+, both; 7-9, pick 1: lesser foes quail/hesitate/flee; doughty foes focus on you as greatest threat. 6-, pick 1 but ask GM what you missed.</p>
          <button type="roll" name="roll_heavy_formidable" value="/em uses Formidable, rolling +CHA [[2d6+@{cha}]]"></button>
        </div>
        <div class="stonetop-move">
          <label><input type="checkbox" name="attr_heavy_frosty"> <strong>Frosty</strong></label>
          <p>When you <em>Defy Danger by keeping calm and carrying on</em>, on a 10+ also ask a Seek Insight question. Advantage on next roll to act on the answer.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="stonetop-move">
          <label><input type="checkbox" name="attr_heavy_guardian"> <strong>Guardian</strong></label>
          <p>When you Defend, hold 1 extra Readiness. Even on a 6-, hold 1 Readiness.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="stonetop-move">
          <label><input type="checkbox" name="attr_heavy_hardtokill" checked> <strong>Hard to Kill ★</strong> (Starting move)</label>
          <p>When <em>at Death's Door</em>, roll +CON or +nothing (your choice). On a 7-9, mark a debility of your choice to regain 1 HP.</p>
          <button type="roll" name="roll_heavy_hardtokill" value="/em uses Hard to Kill, rolling +CON [[2d6+@{con}]]"></button>
        </div>
        <div class="stonetop-move stonetop-move-indent">
          <label><input type="checkbox" name="attr_heavy_unstoppable"> <strong>Unstoppable</strong> (Requires Hard to Kill)</label>
          <p>When reduced to 0 HP in battle, keep fighting. Each hit at 0 HP, mark 1 circle. Regaining HP clears one mark. When you stop, roll Death's Door with -1 per circle marked.</p>
          <div class="stonetop-tracker">
            <span>Marks: </span>
            <input type="checkbox" name="attr_heavy_unstoppable_1">
            <input type="checkbox" name="attr_heavy_unstoppable_2">
            <input type="checkbox" name="attr_heavy_unstoppable_3">
            <input type="checkbox" name="attr_heavy_unstoppable_4">
            <input type="checkbox" name="attr_heavy_unstoppable_5">
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="stonetop-move">
          <label><input type="checkbox" name="attr_heavy_improvedstat"> <strong>Improved Stat</strong> □□□ (up to 3 times)</label>
          <p>Increase one stat by 1 (max +2) each time taken.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="stonetop-move">
          <label><input type="checkbox" name="attr_heavy_intimidating"> <strong>Intimidating</strong></label>
          <p>When you <em>Persuade using violence or threats</em>, you have advantage.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="stonetop-move">
          <label><input type="checkbox" name="attr_heavy_musclebound"> <strong>Musclebound</strong> (Requires STR +2 or higher)</label>
          <p>Hand-to-hand or thrown attacks are <em>forceful</em> and <em>messy</em>. If already forceful/messy, even more so.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="stonetop-move">
          <label><input type="checkbox" name="attr_heavy_payback"> <strong>Payback</strong></label>
          <p>When you <em>deal damage to a foe that harmed you or an ally</em>, deal +1d4 damage.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="stonetop-move">
          <label><input type="checkbox" name="attr_heavy_relentless"> <strong>Relentless</strong></label>
          <p>When you <em>Clash and your foe survives</em>, gain advantage next time you Clash with them.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="stonetop-move">
          <label><input type="checkbox" name="attr_heavy_seasonedwarrior"> <strong>Seasoned Warrior</strong> □□□ (Requires level 2+)</label>
          <p>Take a move from Fox, Marshal, Ranger, or Seeker for which you qualify. Different playbook each time. Not Improved Stat or Superior Stat.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="stonetop-move">
          <label><input type="checkbox" name="attr_heavy_situationalawareness"> <strong>Situational Awareness</strong></label>
          <p>When you Seek Insight, add: biggest threat? enemy's true position? usable weapon? When a fight breaks out, ask the GM 1 Seek Insight question free.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="stonetop-move">
          <label><input type="checkbox" name="attr_heavy_uncannyreflexes"> <strong>Uncanny Reflexes</strong> (Starting choice)</label>
          <p>When unarmored with normal or light load, impose disadvantage on any damage you could dodge or roll with.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="stonetop-move">
          <label><input type="checkbox" name="attr_heavy_unfettered"> <strong>Unfettered</strong></label>
          <p>When subject to <em>physical or mental restraint</em>, mark a debility to immediately break free.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="stonetop-move">
          <label><input type="checkbox" name="attr_heavy_terroronthefield"> <strong>Terror on the Field</strong></label>
          <p>When you <em>reduce a foe to 0 HP</em>, describe how. If particularly brutal or impressive, allies of that foe are impressed, dismayed, or frightened.</p>
        </div>
        <h4>Level 6+ Moves</h4>
        <div class="stonetop-move">
          <label><input type="checkbox" name="attr_heavy_bringerofruin"> <strong>Bringer of Ruin</strong> (Requires level 6+)</label>
          <p>When you <em>roll 12+ to Clash and foe survives</em>, name something they possess — not something that kills them outright. It is broken, shattered, or lost.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="stonetop-move">
          <label><input type="checkbox" name="attr_heavy_cutfromgranite"> <strong>Cut From Granite</strong> (Requires level 6+ and Carved Out of Wood)</label>
          <p>Gain +1 armor (stacks) and +2 max HP (+6 total with Carved Out of Wood).</p>
        </div>
        <div class="stonetop-move">
          <label><input type="checkbox" name="attr_heavy_mightythews"> <strong>Mighty Thews</strong> (Requires level 6+ and Musclebound)</label>
          <p>When you <em>perform a feat of extraordinary strength</em>, you do it — but pick 1: takes a while; causes unwanted damage or harm; takes a toll (mark a debility).</p>
        </div>
        <div class="stonetop-move">
          <label><input type="checkbox" name="attr_heavy_nemesis"> <strong>Nemesis</strong> (Requires level 6+ and Relentless)</label>
          <p>When you <em>Clash and foe survives</em>, all future attacks against them do +1d6 damage.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="stonetop-move">
          <label><input type="checkbox" name="attr_heavy_steadfastguardian"> <strong>Steadfast Guardian</strong> (Requires level 6+ and Guardian)</label>
          <p>While holding Readiness from Defend, you can always suffer damage/effects instead of your ward — no Readiness spend needed.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="stonetop-move">
          <label><input type="checkbox" name="attr_heavy_stonecold"> <strong>Stone Cold</strong> (Requires level 6+ and Frosty)</label>
          <p>When you <em>Defy Danger (or Struggle as One) by keeping calm</em>, treat a 6- as a 7-9.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="stonetop-move">
          <label><input type="checkbox" name="attr_heavy_superiorstat"> <strong>Superior Stat</strong> (Requires level 6+)</label>
          <p>Increase one stat by +1 (max +3).</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <!-- ========== END HEAVY ========== -->

    <!-- ========== FOX PLAYBOOK ========== -->
    <div class="stonetop-playbook-section fox-section">
      <h2>The Fox</h2>
      <p class="playbook-reminder"><strong>Damage:</strong> d8 &nbsp;|&nbsp; <strong>HP Max:</strong> 16</p>
      <p class="playbook-note">You start with <strong>Ambush</strong> OR <strong>Skill at Arms</strong>; <strong>Danger Sense</strong> OR <strong>Perceptive</strong>; and 1 of your choice.</p>
      <h3>Moves</h3>
      <div class="stonetop-moves-list">
        <div class="stonetop-move">
          <label><input type="checkbox" name="attr_fox_allinthewrist"> <strong>All in the Wrist</strong></label>
          <p>Any knife or dagger gets the <em>thrown</em> tag in your hands. You keep a few iron throwing blades (<em>near</em>) on you; they don't take up inventory space. Reset ammo when you Outfit.</p>
          <div class="stonetop-tracker">
            <span>Ammo: </span>
            <input type="checkbox" name="attr_fox_wrist_ammo1">
            <input type="checkbox" name="attr_fox_wrist_ammo2">
            <span class="tracker-label"> (a few left / out)</span>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="stonetop-move">
          <label><input type="checkbox" name="attr_fox_ambush"> <strong>Ambush</strong> (Starting choice)</label>
          <p>When you <em>get the drop on a nearby foe</em>, deal your damage or roll +DEX: 10+, deal damage and pick 2; 7-9, deal damage and pick 1: deal +1d4 damage; stop them raising alarm; slip away before they react; create an opportunity (you or ally gains advantage on next move to act on it).</p>
          <button type="roll" name="roll_fox_ambush" value="/em uses Ambush, rolling +DEX [[2d6+@{dex}]]"></button>
        </div>
        <div class="stonetop-move">
          <label><input type="checkbox" name="attr_fox_burgle"> <strong>Burgle</strong></label>
          <p>When you <em>sneak off alone into a dangerous place</em>, roll +INT: 7+, you make it back and GM says where you got to and what you learned. 10+, also pick 2; 7-9, pick 1: got away clean; swiped something valuable (GM's choice); set something up to exploit; ask a Seek Insight question about what you saw. 6-, you make it back with trouble, or you're missing in action (your call).</p>
          <button type="roll" name="roll_fox_burgle" value="/em uses Burgle, rolling +INT [[2d6+@{int}]]"></button>
        </div>
        <div class="stonetop-move">
          <label><input type="checkbox" name="attr_fox_catlike"> <strong>Catlike</strong></label>
          <p>When you carry a light load and act with care, you move silently. When you hide in shadows or darkness, you remain unseen until you draw attention, move positions, or attack.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="stonetop-move">
          <label><input type="checkbox" name="attr_fox_dabbler"> <strong>Dabbler</strong> □□□ (Requires level 2+)</label>
          <p>Each time taken, choose a move from Heavy, Marshal, Ranger, or Seeker for which you qualify. Not Improved Stat or Superior Stat.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="stonetop-move">
          <label><input type="checkbox" name="attr_fox_dangersense"> <strong>Danger Sense</strong> (Starting choice)</label>
          <p>You can always ask the GM "Is there an ambush or trap here?" If yes, roll +INT: 10+, ask both questions; 7-9, ask 1; either way gain advantage on next roll to act on the answer. What will trigger it? What will happen once triggered? 6-, don't mark XP; you know it's there but nothing bad happens yet.</p>
          <button type="roll" name="roll_fox_dangersense" value="/em uses Danger Sense, rolling +INT [[2d6+@{int}]]"></button>
        </div>
        <div class="stonetop-move">
          <label><input type="checkbox" name="attr_fox_freerunning"> <strong>Free Running</strong></label>
          <p>When you carry a light load and <em>move with speed and grace</em>, gain advantage on any move to surmount or bypass a physical obstacle.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="stonetop-move">
          <label><input type="checkbox" name="attr_fox_improvedstat"> <strong>Improved Stat</strong> □□□ (up to 3 times)</label>
          <p>Increase one stat by 1 (max +2) each time taken.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="stonetop-move">
          <label><input type="checkbox" name="attr_fox_irresistible"> <strong>Irresistible</strong></label>
          <p>When you interact with someone, ask their player if they find you attractive and get an honest answer (usually yes). When you <em>Persuade using your considerable charms as leverage</em>, you have advantage.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="stonetop-move">
          <label><input type="checkbox" name="attr_fox_laughatdanger"> <strong>Laugh at Danger</strong></label>
          <p>When you are about to roll +CON and you <em>make a joke about the adversity you face</em>, you can roll +CHA instead.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="stonetop-move">
          <label><input type="checkbox" name="attr_fox_lightfingers"> <strong>Light Fingers</strong></label>
          <p>When you <em>perform sleight of hand on an unwary mark</em>, you succeed and no one's the wiser. If being watched, roll +DEX: 10+, succeed and no one's the wiser; 7-9, succeed OR no one's the wiser (your choice).</p>
          <button type="roll" name="roll_fox_lightfingers" value="/em uses Light Fingers, rolling +DEX [[2d6+@{dex}]]"></button>
        </div>
        <div class="stonetop-move">
          <label><input type="checkbox" name="attr_fox_perceptive"> <strong>Perceptive</strong> (Starting choice)</label>
          <p>When you Seek Insight, ask 1 additional question. Even on a 6-, ask 1 question (though you might not like how you learn the answer).</p>
        </div>
        <div class="stonetop-move">
          <label><input type="checkbox" name="attr_fox_rapierwit"> <strong>Rapier Wit</strong></label>
          <p>When you <em>pierce an NPC's pride with a well-placed quip</em>, they must pick 1: attack (dealing +1d4 damage if they hit, but giving you advantage on your next roll against them); stoop to your level and respond in kind; spend a few moments fuming or controlling their temper.</p>
